name: Josh Terry
tweet: The problem isn’t, how do we stop a few criminals who might use #bitcoin?  The question is, how can we empower the millions of good people who need bitcoin?

name: Josh Terry
tweet: There are many arguments to be made to show how #Bitcoin could reduce criminal activity on a macro scale.  But that’s not the point.  The point is that bitcoin is busy solving the bigger problem of economic freedom.

name: Josh Terry
tweet: Be careful which injustice you choose to fight. If you aren’t, you may cause even greater harm.  Those who fear that bitcoin may prevent justice being dealt to those who deserve it are ignoring the greater injustice that would occur to everyone else were it not there.  #Bitcoin

name: Josh Terry
tweet: While Blackstone made the point that it’s worth it to allow ten criminals to go free to ensure an innocent man his freedom.  The reality is that there are thousands of people who could be freed by more economic liberties for every one who might be a criminal.  #Bitcoin

name: Josh Terry
tweet: While stopping bad people from doing bad things is important. That’s a small part of what makes the world work.  #Bitcoin is focused on a complex, additive problem of building people up.  Not the more simple problem limiting them.

name: Josh Terry
tweet: Bitcoin makes sure the innocent cannot be financially controlled.  #Bitcoin isn’t focused on stopping criminals. It’s focused on enabling the people who are unjustly imprisoned by a lack of economic freedom.

name: Josh Terry
tweet: In the world today, there are far more innocent than guilty.  And while #Bitcoin might free some of the guilty. Is it worth it to say that bitcoin is bad?  Because to say that you don’t want bitcoin is to chain the innocent for the sake of the guilty.

name: Josh Terry
tweet: Blackstone’s ratio, which values the freedom of an innocent man over the imprisonment of a guilty one, is the foundation of a fair justice system and is a first principle lens to look through when speaking about #bitcoin and criminal behavior.  Namely, freedom is more important.

name: Josh Terry
tweet: If you’re concerned about criminals using #bitcoin think about this quote.  “It is better that ten guilty persons escape than that one innocent suffer.” William Blackstone, one of the founders of modern law.
